title: How have the number of calls resulting in an emergency response changed over time?
analysis_commentary:
Ambulance calls defined as 'Category A' are mainly made up of Red 2 calls; over the time period, 95% were categorised as Red 2 Category A calls and 5% were categorised as Red 1 Category A calls.

When a breach occurs there does appear to be a corresponding increase in the number of calls that are classified as Category A calls.
data_source: NHS England, Ambulance Quality Indicators: System Indicators
